x
x \lor (\lnot x \land y)
(x \land y) \lor (x \land \lnot y) \equiv x \land (y \lor \lnot y) = x
x \lor (\lnot x \land y)\equiv (x \lor \lnot x) \land (x \lor y) \equiv x \lor y
(x \land y) \lor (x \land \lnot y) = x
(x \land y) \lor (x \land \lnot y) \lor (\lnot x \land y) = x \lor (\lnot x \land y)
x = x \lor (x \land y)
x \lor (\lnot x \land y) = x \lor (x \land y) \lor (\lnot x \land y) 
( x \land y ) \lor (\lnot x \land y) = y
x \lor ( x \land y ) \lor (\lnot x \land  y)  = x \lor y
